
<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Cloudflare API Credentials</h1>
    <div class="form-actions">
        <a href="[% c.uri_for('/admin/site_provisioning') %]" class="btn btn-secondary">&#8592; Site Provisioning</a>
    </div>
</div>

[% IF c.flash.error_msg %]
<div class="error-message">[% c.flash.error_msg | html %]</div>
[% END %]
[% IF c.flash.success_msg %]
<div class="success-message">[% c.flash.success_msg | html %]</div>
[% END %]

<div class="content-container">
<div class="content-primary">
<div class="data-container">

<div class="form-section">
    <h3>Storage Location</h3>
    <p>Credentials are stored in the <code>app_secrets</code> database table — shared across all branches, servers, and Docker containers. No env files required.</p>
    <p>Status: [% IF token_set %]<span class="status-badge status-active">&#10003; API token is set</span>[% ELSE %]<span class="status-badge status-pending">&#9888; Token not set or placeholder</span>[% END %]</p>
</div>

<div class="form-container">
<form method="post" action="[% c.uri_for('/admin/site_provisioning/cf_settings') %]" class="app-form">

    <div class="form-section">
        <h3>Cloudflare API Token</h3>
        <p class="form-hint">
            &#9888; <strong>This is NOT the Cloudflare Tunnel token.</strong>
            Create a <strong>DNS API token</strong> at
            <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens" target="_blank">Cloudflare → My Profile → API Tokens</a>
            — use the <em>"Edit zone DNS"</em> template → permissions: <strong>Zone → DNS → Edit</strong> on all zones.
            The token will be ~40 alphanumeric characters (not a UUID).
        </p>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-field">
                <label for="api_token">API Token[% IF token_set %] <small>(currently set — enter new value to replace)</small>[% END %]</label>
                <input type="password" id="api_token" name="api_token" class="form-input"
                       placeholder="[% IF token_set %]Leave blank to keep current token[% ELSE %]Paste your Cloudflare API token here[% END %]"
                       autocomplete="off">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-field">
                <label for="email">Cloudflare Account Email</label>
                <input type="email" id="email" name="email" class="form-input"
                       value="[% cf_email | html %]"
                       placeholder="e.g. shantamcbain@gmail.com">
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="form-actions">
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">&#10003; Save Credentials</button>
        <a href="[% c.uri_for('/admin/site_provisioning') %]" class="btn btn-secondary">Cancel</a>
    </div>

</form>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</div>
